frameDefinitions: An Agent actively maintains or improves their level of phyiscal fitness.
This frame describes food and meal preparation.
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
An Inspector attains a degree of certainty in the Unconfirmed_content, generally by inspecting some evidence.
A Cause or Agent causes a Patient to undergo a change of phase.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.

listRoleDefinitions: The person who is trying to improve or maintain their physical fitness.
The time that the <fen>Agent</fen> exercises.
The location of the Agent while exercising.
The <fen>Cook</fen>  prepares the <fen>Produced_food</fen>.

This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the cooking creation occurs.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.

An open proposition that the <fen>Inspector</fen> decides by examining evidence.  It is usually a propostion put forward which some parties would disbelieve or contest.
The <fen>Medium</fen> is the piece of text or work in which the <fen>Inspector</fen> verifies the <fen>Unconfirmed_content</fen>:
This role describes the <fen>Time</fen> at which the verification event takes place.
This role describes where the verificiation event takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to change phase.

This role identifies the Time at which the change of phase occurs.
This role identifies the place where change of phase occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.

The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
